<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1964-12-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1964-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="266" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d266">
                        <head>266. Letter From Secretary of the Treasury <persName corresp="#p_DCD1" type="from">Dillon</persName> to Secretary of Commerce <persName corresp="#p_HLH1" type="to">Hodges</persName><note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d266fn1">Source: Washington National Records
                                Center, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 40, Secretary of Commerce
                                Files: <gloss target="#t_FRC1">FRC</gloss> 69 A 6828, Treasury
                                Department. No classification marking.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1964-12-04">December 4, 1964</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Dear <persName corresp="#p_HLH1">Luther</persName>:</p>
                        <p>Your letter of December 2, 1964, asks where we stand on the Canadian auto
                            parts question.<note n="2" xml:id="d266fn2">
                                <persName corresp="#p_HLH1">Hodges</persName>’ December 2 letter to
                                    <persName corresp="#p_DCD1">Dillon</persName> is ibid.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>In a meeting held in <persName corresp="#p_BGW1">George Ball</persName>’s
                            office on Monday, November 23, which you were unable to attend, there
                            was full agreement that countervailing duties should be imposed in early
                            January if the problem arising from the Canadian rebate plan has not
                            been solved before that time.<note n="3" xml:id="d266fn3">No other
                                record of this November 23 meeting has been found.</note>
                            <pb facs="0719" n="689" xml:id="pg_689"/> Before taking such action,
                            Treasury would, of course, advise the White House and the Departments of
                            State and Commerce.</p>
                        <p>With best wishes,</p>
                        <p>Sincerely,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_DCD1">
                                    <hi rend="strong">Douglas</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>